	<dl>
	<dt>In truth, I will vote, as long as my...</dt>
	<dd><p>In truth, I will vote, as long as my voting card arrives.  I also believe that voting should be compulsory, even if you spoil your ballot paper or they add a 'none of the above' option (preferably with an option to say why).<br />Whilst this site seems to be proving that there are a large number of people who choose not to vote for a variety of reasons (some clearly more valid than others), I'm sorry to say that of the proportion of people who don't vote at all, I'm convinced that the majority of non-voters fail to turn out because they simply can't be arsed.</p>
	<small>
	written 14th Apr 2005 <!--  | <a href="../email/801">Email this
    to a friend</a> | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=801">abusive?</a> -->
	</small>
	</dd>
	</dl>

